BBC World Service</link></network>
 in 1968, he has spent his entire professional career with the Corporation. Yentob has two children, Isabella and Jacob.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref>.
<sec>
<st>
Career</st>
<p>

In 1973, Yentob became a <occupation wordnetid="100582388" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
